column8: Remarks
Original definition of a and b in feet. OSGB defines 1/f to 7 d.p.
Clarke 1858/II solution. Derived parameters: a = 6378293.639m; 1/f = 294.26068
Uses Benoit 1896 foot-metre ratio. Derived parameter: 1/f = 294.97870
Uses Benoit 1896 inch-metre ratio. Derived parameter: 1/f = 293.46623
Used in Old French Triangulation (ATF).
Used for the 1937 adjustment of Indian triangulation
Adopted 1967 for use in East Malaysia. Uses Sears 1928 inch-metre ratio.
Used by Surveys of India and Pakistan since 1975. Derived parameter: 1/f = 300.80174
Adopted 1967 for use in West Malaysia. Uses Benoit 1898 inch-metre ratio.
Used for  GEM 10C Gravity Potential Model.
Adopted by IUGG 1979 Canberra.
Helmert 1906/III solution.
Adopted by IUGG 1924 in Madrid. Based on Hayford 1909/1910 figures.
Adopted by IUGG 1967 Lucerne. Inverse flattening defined to 2 d.p.
Used by Transit Broadcast Ephemeris before 1989. Also referred to as WGS72 spheroid.
Used by Transit Precise Ephemeris between October 1971 and January 1987.
Used for OSU86 gravity potential (geoidal) model.
Used for OSU91 gravity potential (geoidal) model.
